---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words Ending With Z — Top Scoring Z-Ending Words"
  description="Discover the highest-scoring Scrabble words ending with Z. Free list of top Z-ending words with point values and strategy tips. No signup required."
  keywords="scrabble words ending with z, words ending in z scrabble, z ending words, high scoring words ending z, scrabble word list"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Words Ending With Z — Top Highest-Scoring Z-Ending Words",
    "description": "Discover the highest-scoring Scrabble words ending with Z. Complete list with point values and board strategy.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-ending-with-z" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the highest-scoring Scrabble word ending with Z?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "PIZZAZZ scores 45 points without premium squares — one of the highest-scoring words in the entire game. JAZZ (29 points) and FIZZ (25 points) are also extremely powerful Z-ending plays using double Z tiles." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many Z tiles are in a Scrabble set?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "There is only 1 Z tile in a standard Scrabble set, worth 10 points. However, you can use a blank tile as a Z (scoring 0 for that tile). Words with double Z like JAZZ and BUZZ require the blank as the second Z." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are words ending in ZZ valid in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — JAZZ, BUZZ, FIZZ, FUZZ, and PIZZAZZ are all valid. Since there's only one Z tile, you need a blank for the second Z. These words score extremely well even with the blank counting as 0 points." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">More Letter Guides</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending With Z — Top Highest-Scoring Z-Ending Words</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Z is the joint highest-value tile in Scrabble at 10 points, and words ending in Z deliver some of the most explosive scores possible. From the legendary JAZZ and BUZZ to more accessible plays like QUIZ and WALTZ, Z-ending words combine raw point power with board-blocking potential. These are the plays that can swing an entire game in a single turn.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 30 Highest-Scoring Words Ending With Z</h2>
      <p>These are the most valuable words ending in Z, ranked by base point value. The Z tile's 10-point value makes every Z-ending word a potential game-changer.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Length</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PIZZAZZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">45</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">JAZZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">29</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">FIZZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">25</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">FUZZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">25</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BUZZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">24</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUIZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">22</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">WALTZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">HERTZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">TOPAZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">16</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BLITZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">16</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why Z-Ending Words Matter in Scrabble</h2>
      <p>Z-ending words represent the pinnacle of Scrabble scoring efficiency. With Z worth 10 points — tied with Q for the highest tile value — any word ending in Z starts with a massive built-in advantage. When that Z lands on a double or triple letter square, you're looking at 20 or 30 points from a single tile placement. JAZZ on a triple-letter Z scores 49 points for a 4-letter word.</p>
      <p>The double-Z words (JAZZ, BUZZ, FIZZ, FUZZ) require a blank tile for the second Z, but they're still incredibly powerful. Even with the blank scoring 0, JAZZ still delivers 19 points (J=8, A=1, Z=10, blank=0) — and that's before any premium squares. The strategic value goes beyond points: Z-ending words are completely unhookable, creating dead ends on the board that protect adjacent premium squares from opponent exploitation.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Save blanks for double-Z words:</strong> If you have Z + blank, JAZZ (29 pts) and FIZZ (25 pts) are among the highest-scoring 4-letter words possible. This combo is worth holding tiles for.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>WALTZ doesn't need a blank:</strong> At 17 points with common tiles (W, A, L, T, Z), WALTZ is accessible without requiring the blank tile for a double-Z.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Target TLS with Z:</strong> Z on a triple-letter square = 30 points from one tile. WALTZ with Z on TLS scores 37 points. Always scan for these opportunities.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>QUIZ is your Q+Z power play:</strong> If you have both Q and Z, QUIZ (22 pts) deploys both premium tiles in one turn. That's 20 points from just Q and Z alone.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Block with Z-endings:</strong> Nothing extends past Z. Place Z-ending words to seal off premium square access for your opponent while banking big points yourself.</span></li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-with-x" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending With X — Top Scoring X-Ending Words</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-q" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Containing Q — Top Scoring Q Words</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-with-e" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending With E — Top Scoring E-Ending Words</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
